                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Beauty hunt reaches Orissa
  - SANANDA TILOTTAMA PRELIMS IN BHUBANESWAR          OUR CORRESPONDENT                          Actress Madhumita Mohanty unveils Sananda Tilottama beauty pageant in Bhubaneswar on Tuesday. Picture by Sanjib Mukherjee                                        
	Bhubaneswar, June 1: The hunt for eastern Indias most glamorous beauty is on and there could not be happier news for wannabe models or actresses in Orissa.        
	Sananda Tilottama, eastern Indias biggest and most prestigious beauty pageant  that boasts of a lineage that has names such as Bipasha Basu, Koena Mitra, Celina Jaitley, Reshhmi Ghosh, Nicollette Bird, Jyoti Brahmin, Dimpy Ganguly among others will conduct the prelims of the pageant here for the first time.        
	Following the overwhelming number of entries received from Orissa, we have decided to hold the pageants here this year, said an official, adding that the date of the prelims would be announced shortly.        
	Prelims will be held in Bhubaneswar and Jamshedpur in addition to Calcutta and Guwahati. A mega preliminary round comprising shortlisted contestants will be held in Calcutta, said the official.                                                                                                                                                           
